"Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Carter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name for a transporter of goods, from Middle English <i>carter(e)</i> ‘carter’ (Anglo-Norman French <i>car(e)tier</i>, Old French <i>charetier</i>, medieval Latin <i>carettarius</i>, <i>carettator</i>). The Old French word coalesced with the earlier Middle English word <i>cart(e)</i> ‘cart’, which is from either Old Norse <i>kartr</i> or Old English <i>cræt</i>, both of which, like the Late Latin word, were probably derived from Celtic. This surname is also very common among African Americans.","Irish: shortened form of   McCarter  .","Americanized form of German   Karter   ‘carder’."],"variants":[{"name":"Charman","meanings":["English (Sussex and Surrey): occupational name for a carter, carrier, or coachman, from Middle English (Old French) <i>char</i>, <i>car</i> ‘car, cart, carriage’ + Middle English <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   Carter   and   Carman   2.","English (Sussex and Surrey): occupational name for someone who did odd jobs, from Middle English <i>char(re)</i>, <i>chere</i> (Old English <i>cier(r)</i>, <i>cer(r)</i>, <i>cear(r)</i>, <i>cær(r)</i>) ‘turn (of activity), small job, chore’ + <i>man</i>. Compare   Carman   2.","In some cases probably also an Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Čarman</b> (see   Carman   5)."]},{"name":"Chartier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Armand, Normand, Jacques, Marcel, Adelard, Alcide, Emile, Gilles, Raoul, Rosaire, Alphonse.","French: shortened form of <i>charretier</i>, an occupational name for a carter, from an agent derivative of Old French <i>charette</i> ‘cart’.","French Canadian: altered form of English   Carter  , a cognate of 1 above. Compare   Sharkey   and   Shorkey  ."]},{"name":"Karter","meanings":["German: occupational name for a carder (someone who prepares wool for spinning), from Middle High German <i>karter</i>. Compare   Carter  ."]},{"name":"McCarter","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   McArthur  ."]},{"name":"Carrier","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Andre, Marcel, Emile, Lucien, Cecile, Alain, Gaetan, Gilles, Jacques, Laurent, Normand.","English and southern French: from Middle English, Old French <i>car(r)ier</i> (from Late Latin <i>carrarius</i>, a derivative of <i>carrum</i> ‘cart, wagon’, a word of Gaulish origin), an occupational name for a carter (see   Carter  ), in French also for a cartwright. Compare French   Charrier  .","French: occupational name for a stonemason or quarryman, <i>carrier</i>. Compare   Coyer  ."]},{"name":"Cartman","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): occupational name from Middle English <i>cartman</i> ‘man who operated a cart for the transport of goods’. Compare   Carter  .","Americanized form of German <b>Kartmann</b> (see   Kartman  )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":5,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":18,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":27,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Carter was born about 1310, in England. He had at least 1 son with Carter."},"et":{"abt 1310–":"umbes 1310–Surnud","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1336–1387":"1336–1387","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1310":"1310","abt 1310":"umbes 1310","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beverley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"abt 1310–":"noin 1310–Kuollut","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1336–1387":"1336–1387","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1310":"1310","abt 1310":"noin 1310","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beverley, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"abt 1310–":"environ 1310–Décédé","1310–Female":"1310–Décédée","1336–1387":"1336–1387","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1310":"1310","abt 1310":"environ 1310","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beverley, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Carter est né environ 1310, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Carter."},"de":{"abt 1310–":"um 1310–Verstorben","1310–Female":"1310–Verstorben","1336–1387":"1336–1387","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1336":"1336","1453":"1453","1387":"1387","1310":"1310","abt 1310":"um 1310","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beverley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Carter wurde um 1310 in England geboren. Er hatte mit Carter mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"abt 1310–":"about 1310–Desede","1310–Female":"1310–Desede","1336–1387":"1336–1387","1310–Male":"1310–Desede","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1